\\n\\nI'm thinking about whether adding Jansi 1.18 affects the native image configuration. It doesn’t appear to contain resource-config, but there’s a chance that using a native image with the ServiceLoader for PropertySource could force class initialization during the image build. If tests build the native image after running the agent, it might use the service configuration and initialize PropertiesUtil due to Log4j's static initialization. The FORCE_WINDOWS_PROPERTY is defaulting to null, which means there won't be any Windows-specific behavior.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering test instructions**\\n\\nI’m thinking I might not need to run any tests based on the instructions. But maybe I should mention that I didn’t run them at all. It could also be helpful to include the files that were changed. There’s an existing uncommitted ReflectionUtilTest that I haven't touched, and while I could skip mentioning it, transparency seems important. It’s all about ensuring clear communication!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented focused ConsoleAppender dynamic-access coverage for `org.apache.logging.log4j:log4j-core:2.17.1`.\n\nChanges made:\n- Added `ConsoleAppenderTest.java` under:\n  - `tests/src/org.apache.logging.log4j/log4j-core/2.17.1/src/test/java/org_apache_logging_log4j/log4j_core/`\n- Added a test `PropertySource` service resource to make Log4j’s `PropertiesUtil` see a Windows OS only during this test:\n  - `tests/src/org.apache.logging.log4j/log4j-core/2.17.1/src/test/resources/META-INF/services/org.apache.logging.log4j.util.PropertySource`\n- Added the Jansi dependency needed for `org.fusesource.jansi.WindowsAnsiOutputStream` lookup:\n  - `tests/src/org.apache.logging.log4j/log4j-core/2.17.1/build.gradle`\n\nThe new test builds a `ConsoleAppender` with Jansi enabled and `direct=false`, exercising:\n- `Class#getConstructor(OutputStream.class)`\n- `Constructor#newInstance(outputStream)`\n\nIt also handles expected Jansi platform initialization errors from forcing the Windows-specific path on non-Windows runtimes, after the dynamic-access call sites have been reached.\n\nI did not compile or run tests, per instruction.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0bf8d8b01c02a1f1016a0da396692481979dea7c75689f62c3\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 457, "output": 1275, "cacheRead": 46080, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 47812, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1779278723629, "responseId": "resp_0bf8d8b01c02a1f1016a0da3843c6c819781348cb38f616fcb"}, "toolResults": []}
